+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KE8uWcZ3P6ARFxAkndTBKj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No checkpoint found, and I have a clear picture of the project. The environment is set up with all dependencies. Since `CONCLAVE_NON_INTERACTIVE=1` applies in this headless benchmark, I'll use Autopilot mode.\n\nNon-interactive mode: using Autopilot.\n\nLet me make the key design decisions:\n\n**Q: OT vs CRDT for conflict resolution?**\n→ Choosing: Operational Transform (OT) with position-based text operations\n  Reasoning: OT is simpler to implement correctly for text editing, well-understood for insert/delete ops, and the TASK.md mentions OT specifically. A simple server-authoritative OT model (where the server transforms and applies ops sequentially) avoids the complexity of peer-to-peer CRDTs.\n\n**Q: WebSocket integration with Express?**\n→ Choosing: Upgrade HTTP server with `ws` WebSocketServer using `handleProtocols` on the HTTP server's `upgrade` event, with URL-based document routing.\n  Reasoning: Clean separation, no extra libraries needed, works with the existing Express setup.\n\n**Q: Server architecture?**\n→ Choosing: Single-module with `createApp` factory, DocumentManager class for in-memory doc state + OT transforms, SQLite for persistence.\n\nNow let me invoke the TDD skill to implement this."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1011,"cache_read_input_tokens":22610,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1011},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4228706-d4c1-40ce-b921-56d892cabeec","uuid":"a3edc09a-fe7c-4b33-8c1c-061a84bc34d9"}
